## Interface Contracts

These specs are fixed. Both developers code to these exactly.

### FC Matrix Files
```
Location:  ~/Desktop/DATA_clinical/fc_matrices/
Filename:  sub-002_condition-attend_positive_FC.npy
Shape:     (200, 200)
Dtype:     float32
Values:    Fisher Z-transformed Pearson correlations
Diagonal:  set to 0
```

### ROI Time Series Files
```
Location:  ~/Desktop/DATA_clinical/roi_timeseries/
Filename:  sub-002_task-epr_schaefer200.csv
Shape:     (834, 200)
Columns:   parcel_001 ... parcel_200
Index:     TR index (0-833)
```

### Clinical Clean CSV
```
Location:  ~/Desktop/DATA_clinical/clinical_clean.csv
Columns:   subject_id, group, age, vas_pain, hamd_total, hamd_cat,
           hama_total, tas_total, tas_dif, tas_ddf, tas_eot,
           alexithymia, erq_reappraisal, erq_suppression
subject_id: sub-002 format (zero-padded to 3 digits)
group:      FM or HC (string, not 0/1)
Rows:       63 (excludes sub-005, sub-012, sub-032)
```

### PyG Data Object (output of dataset.__getitem__)
```
data.x:          node features       [200, 5]   float32
data.edge_index: graph connectivity  [2, E]     long
data.edge_attr:  edge weights        [E]        float32
data.y:          group label         [1]        long    (0=FM, 1=HC)
data.subject_id: subject identifier  string     e.g. 'sub-002'
data.condition:  condition label     string     e.g. 'attend_positive'
```

### GAT Encoder Output
```
Input:   PyG Batch object
Output:  torch.Tensor [batch_size, 64]  float32
```

### Embeddings Dictionary
```
Key:    subject_id string  e.g. 'sub-002'
Value:  torch.Tensor [9, 64]  float32
        rows ordered: attend_positive, attend_negative, attend_neutral,
                      reappraise_positive, reappraise_negative, reappraise_neutral,
                      suppress_positive, suppress_negative, suppress_neutral
```

### Cluster Labels Array
```
Type:   numpy array [63]  int
Values: 0, 1, or 2
Order:  must match row order of clinical_clean.csv exactly
```

### Attention Pool Output
```
Input:   torch.Tensor [9, 64]  float32  (9 condition embeddings)
Output:  torch.Tensor [64]     float32  (pooled subject embedding)
Weights: torch.Tensor [9]      float32  (sum to 1.0)
```

